1. JAVA CLASS loading
   JVM loads .class files
   CLASS will be loaded when using new to create an object of a specific CLASS, accessing static member of specific CLASS or accessing subCLASS
   loading file into memory
   linking : allocate memory for Class Varables and translate symbolic reference to memory address
   initialization : call construction function
2. JAVA CLASS unloading
   JVM executes CLASS unloading automatically when it is unused
3. variables
   local : located in stack. JVM will recycle this type of variables
   object : located in heap. belongs to diffent instantiated objects of a CLASS
            every object has a copy of this variable
   class/static : located in static memory space. belongs to class and has same life span as the whole programe.

